# Copy to .env.railway (same folder as backend/.env) — file is gitignored.
# Used by: npm run reset-admin-users  (loads after .env; overrides DATABASE_URL)
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Hostname postgres.railway.internal only works INSIDE Railway's network (API container).
# - To run scripts from your Mac/PC, use the PUBLIC connection string from:
#   Railway → Postgres service → Connect → "Public Network" / TCP proxy URL
#   (often looks like *.rlwy.net or a public host + port).
#
# One line only:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:PASSWORD@PUBLIC_HOST:PORT/railway
